The paper discusses the use of neural networks in constituency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also focuses on the use of recurrent neural networks, which falls under the subcategory of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of general-purpose neural machinery, which is a topic in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
